snippet: Lawyers for New York City said in a court filing on Tuesday that they expected to resume settlement talks in the lawsuit by five men convicted in the 1989 rape of a jogger in Central Park.
abstract: Lawyers for New York City say in court filing they expect to resume settlement talks in protracted lawsuit by five men convicted in 1989 rape of jogger in Central Park; say they will work to resolve case by end of May.
lead_paragraph: Lawyers for New York City said in a court filing on Tuesday that they expected to resume settlement talks in the lawsuit by five men convicted in the 1989 rape of a jogger in Central Park.

headline.main: More Talks Expected in ‘Central Park Five’ Lawsuit
headline.print_headline: More Talks Expected in Rape Lawsuit
